      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must closely replicate VAD operating envelope including fluid temperature, hematocrit range, and rotational speed range.",
      "rationale": "Bench experiments used bovine blood at a single hematocrit value (35%) and ambient temperature; VAD operating conditions span 33–45% hematocrit and physiological temperature. Mismatch reduces confidence in absolute hemolysis extrapolation. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of predicted versus measured hemolysis index must include uncertainty bounds on both simulation and experimental data, with agreement within 20% across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted hemolysis index deviates from experimental values by 18–47% across operating points. Uncertainty bounds on experimental data are not fully reported. Achieved level 2 is substantially below the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary quantity of interest (absolute hemolysis index) must be directly measurable in validation experiments and directly computed by the simulation without surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is computed directly from the power-law model integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks, consistent with experimental measurement. However, the Lagrangian sampling density is insufficient at high-shear blade tip regions. Achieved level 3 falls short of required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
