      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The power-law hemolysis model must be shown to be the appropriate model form for the flow regimes encountered in the VAD, including transitional and turbulent shear environments.",
      "rationale": "No systematic comparison of alternative hemolysis model forms (e.g., strain-based, energy dissipation-based) was performed. The power-law model is used without justification of its applicability across the full operating envelope. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
